# Frontend Development Guidelines

## Angular Structure
- **Components**: Located in `src/app/modules/components/`
- **Configuration**: Loaded from [src/schedule-config.json](mdc:Yogkit/src/schedule-config.json)
- **Global Styles**: [src/styles.scss](mdc:Yogkit/src/styles.scss)
- **Assets**: [src/assets/](mdc:Yogkit/src/assets/) for images, CSS, JS

## Component Guidelines
- **Home View**: Main landing page component in [src/app/modules/components/home-view/](mdc:Yogkit/src/app/modules/components/home-view/)
- **Responsive Design**: Use Bootstrap classes and custom SCSS
- **Configuration Binding**: Use `{{ config?.section?.property }}` syntax for dynamic content

## Styling Patterns
- **Color Scheme**: 
  - Primary: `rgb(147, 75, 19)` (dark brown)
  - Background: `rgb(254, 248, 238)` (light cream)
  - Text: `#000000` (black)
- **Typography**: 
  - Headings: 'Playfair Display', serif
  - Body: 'Poppins', sans-serif
- **Responsive Breakpoints**: 
  - Mobile: `max-width: 768px`
  - Tablet: `max-width: 1024px`
  - Desktop: `min-width: 1200px`

## Image Handling
- **Hero Image**: [src/assets/image/trainer_lotus.svg](mdc:Yogkit/src/assets/image/trainer_lotus.svg)
- **Positioning**: Use `top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%)` for vertical centering
- **Responsive**: Scale images appropriately for different screen sizes
- **Overflow**: Set `overflow: visible` to prevent image clipping

## Configuration Integration
- **Dynamic Content**: All text content should be configurable via the admin backend
- **Fallback Values**: Always provide fallback values in templates
- **Loading States**: Handle configuration loading gracefully

## CSS Best Practices
- **SCSS Variables**: Use CSS custom properties for consistent theming
- **Mobile First**: Start with mobile styles and enhance for larger screens
- **Flexbox/Grid**: Use modern CSS layout techniques
- **Transitions**: Add smooth transitions for better UX

## Component Communication
- **Service Pattern**: Use Angular services for data management
- **Configuration Service**: Centralized config loading and caching
- **Event Handling**: Use Angular event binding for user interactions
